  "body": "Version: 0.9\r\nOS: Windows 10\r\n\r\nClicking anywhere outside a modal dialogue should close it. This functionality currently doesnâ€™t work for the modal dialogs listed below. \r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\n<ins>Steps to reproduce:</ins>\r\n\r\n1. Navigate to:\r\n\r\n- Setting/Profile/Change Password\r\n- Setting/Keycard/Setup a new Keycard with an existing account\r\n- Setting/Keycard/Create a new Keycard account with a new seed phrase\r\n- Setting/Keycard/Import or restore via a seed phrase\r\n- Setting/Keycard/Import from Keycard to Status Desktop\r\n- Setting/Keycard/Check whatâ€™s on a Keycard\r\n-  Setting/Keycard/Factory reset a Keycard\r\n- Wallet/Add account\r\n\r\n<ins>What currently incorrectly happens:</ins>\r\n\r\nIf the user clicks anywhere outside of the modal dialog, nothing happens.  \r\n\r\n<ins>What is supposed to happen:</ins>\r\n\r\nIf the user clicks anywhere outside of the modal dialog, the modal dialogue should close.\r\n\r\n<ins>Other information</ins>\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/124154641/222198332-429d0614-bde4-4ab9-9204-a451e3a12c3d.mp4\r\n",
