    "body": "Good point, thanks for your reply ðŸ™‚ \r\n\r\nGiven the usecase that you have correctly pointed out, lets amend the change request to the following; \r\n\r\n\"Clicking anywhere outside a modal dialogue which has a close 'x' **visible** in the top right corner, should close the dialogue.  e.g. if there is a close 'x' visible, clicking outside of the modal dialogue should be equivalent to clicking the close 'x'\".\r\n\r\nModal dialogues that currently have a close 'x', but where clicking outside doesn't close them (but should if the 'x' is visible):\r\n\r\n- Change password dialogue where the user enters their new password (as the user should be able to exit by closing the dialogue before they click the \"Change password and restart Status\" button.\r\n\r\n- Wallet 'Add account' dialogue.\r\n\r\n- All 'keycard dialogues' listed in the original issue report (but only when a close 'x' is visible in the dialogue of course).\r\n\r\nTo summarize, if a user isn't able to close a dialogue by clicking on an 'x' then clicking outside the dialogue should do nothing, but if a user is able to close the dialogue by clicking on an 'x', then clicking outside the dialogue (as an alternative to clicking the 'X) should close the dialogue. \r\n",
